    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CUMMINS CELECT - 1992-1993 - TROUBLESHOOTING - VEHICLE SPEED SENSOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>VEHICLE SPEED SENSOR</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>When monitoring engine functions with a DDR, if the vehicle is moving the miles-per-hour will display
                as MPH=XXX (actual vehicle speed if operating properly). To test the sensor and circuits use the
                following charts. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08143_5.xml" xrefid="x0814313">paragraph Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</hotlnk>
                for operation description of sensor and circuit.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor Test</title>
            <figure id="f0814352" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814352" filename="../figg08/g0814352.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuit Test</title>
            <figure id="f0814353" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814353" filename="../figg08/g0814353.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0814354" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814354" filename="../figg08/g0814354.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting Speedometer Sensor</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect both sensor leads, loosen locknut and remove sensor from rear of
                    transmission.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The sensor, leads and connectors should be free of damage. Remove any metal shavings or
                    debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn it in until it contacts the transmission speedometer gear,
                    then back off 1 FULL TURN.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten lock nut to 15 ft. lbs. (20.3 N&#183; m) and connect both leads.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
